title: Stock Market Today: Records, Metals Mania and Mixed Tech Tape
author: Itai Smidt
description: U.S. stock indices hover near record highs on Christmas Eve with the S&P 500 up 0.1% and year-to-date gains of 17.5%. Precious metals surge with gold breaking above $4,500/oz (up 70% YTD) and silver up 150%. The market shows mixed tech performance with AI leaders like Nvidia and Alphabet driving gains, while Intel faces pressure after Nvidia halts testing of its 18A process. Strong Q3 GDP growth of 4.3% and falling jobless claims support the bull case, though consumer confidence remains weak. The market is in late-cycle territory with valuations rich and stock selection critical.

title: Exploring the Silver Rally: 3 Key Factors Driving Up Prices
author: Shane Neagle
description: Silver has surged approximately 158% year-to-date, crossing the $75-per-ounce threshold for the first time and becoming the third-most valuable asset globally. The rally is driven by three key factors: escalating geopolitical risks boosting safe-haven demand, sustained central bank purchases and ETF inflows, and a structural supply deficit of approximately 800 million ounces over the last five years. Lower Federal Reserve interest rates and robust industrial demand from solar panel manufacturers further support the bull market, though near-term corrections remain possible.

description: Intel's 18A process node and expanded Arizona manufacturing capacity position the company to challenge TSMC's dominance in 2026. With strong demand for data center products and expected significant earnings growth, Intel could deliver stronger gains than the modest 10% analyst price target suggests, though valuation multiples remain elevated.

title: Investing Legend Warren Buffett Bids Adieu to Wall Street, While His Trillion-Dollar Company, Berkshire Hathaway, Enters a New Era
author: Sean Williams
description: Warren Buffett steps down as CEO of Berkshire Hathaway on December 31, 2025, after 60+ years, with Greg Abel taking over. Despite being a net seller of stocks for 12 quarters, Buffett's value-focused philosophy and long-term approach nearly doubled S&P 500 returns. Abel is expected to continue this strategy while potentially expanding into technology and healthcare sectors, though some core holdings like Apple may be reconsidered.
